editorialSummary.text: Relaxed option for hearty, homestyle Italian cooking offered over the counter or delivered.

originalText.text: Ah Lena's, a reliable neighborhood staple to satisfy all my Italian cravings. Sure, prices are a tad high and might turn some away, but the portions are huge, and if evaluated based on price of bite ratio, it's actually very well-priced. Think of it as: you'll def have leftovers, which you'll definitely want, since some of the dishes shine even more after the sauces have marinated a bit more. Not sure why I never wrote a review despite getting takeout from them for years; might be guilty of gatekeeping. Shhh. For tonight's Sunday night "don't feel like cooking let's order delivery to nourish our souls for the upcoming workweek," I got the pasta fiorentina with rigatoni (ALWAYS rigatoni for this dish because it takes up the sauce better), and a tiramisu. I always ask for extra sauce w the fiorentina - and always save the extra sauce to toss w my own rigatoni during the week (I know, it's genius right? It's tasty AND I solved one weekday meal); had a hankering for tiramisu because social media has been showing me a friend's trip around Italy and I'm drooling jealousy. Lena's tiramisu isn't life altering or mind blowing, but it does the job as a pick me up. Service is always quick. Food is always consistently good.

originalText.text: I ordered takeout from here and it was excellent! The food was delicious and the portions are huge. I thought the vodka sauce was done very nicely, not too thick or oily, and had green onion for some crunch. Also, not sure if it was the restaurant, but the food came super quickly, which was awesome. Overall, I recommend ordering out from here and I hope this helps!
